item.title: CVE-2023-45292|2024-08-02T20:21:15.289Z -- github.com%2Fmojocn%2Fbase64captcha -- github.com%2Fmojocn%2Fbase64captcha
item.description: When using the default implementation of Verify to check a Captcha, verification can be bypassed. For example, if the first parameter is a non-existent id, the second parameter is an empty string, and the third parameter is true, the function will always consider the Captcha to be correct.
